I like this place, I've been here twice now for lunch. The first time we sat upstairs outside. They have a great patio spot with tons of seating and huge sliding doors to make the inside feel like it's outside.  Very nice and has a different vibe than other patio areas.  Today I did carry out which worked really well.  Used the Ritual App to order and picked up with a couple coworkers.  I knocked off one star bc the falafel just isn't my favorite. It's a little hard and I don't like that they don't smush it (you either smush or you don't, I like it smushed. Helps for "eatability" :))  Their "handhelds" aren't handhelds; way too big and stuffed. I mean that's good, but most definitely not a sandwich. It's a fork and knife deal so don't take it for travelling or anything like that.  Prices are great for what you get.  I'll still go back but I like Roti's falafel better.

I was really craving some healthy, but delicious lunch that wasn't too heavy. Decided to try this place since it just opened and boasted a rooftop bar. I went for the lamb & beef handheld. The meat itself wasn't amazing, but I love that you have the option to add fries in your handheld. I added feta, fries, tomatoes & cucumber, baba ghanoush, chopped romaine and vinegar pickles--- a superb combination and I was full until about 6 PM--- and all for $7.45--- what a steal! I'll definitely come back and get another handheld, but try the falafel next time. Ughhh thinking about it makes me crave it now.  Fast service. The bar upstairs is pretty nice--- they have a separate menu and the cocktails are priced pretty cheaply. I'll definitely come back in the summer!

Everything was average.  Normally when food is catered I give it the benefit of the doubt but this place is only 1 block away. The office I work in ordered MANY things for lunch one day and it was just ok.  The falafel was hard and dry. Luckily, the hummus was good(a lot of garlic which I enjoy) which helped it go down. The vegetables were very bitter, especially the eggplant.  The chicken on the kabob was good but it was ruined by the acidic onions on the skewers. I'd recommend ditching all of the vegetables until they figure out a way to balance the acidic nature of them.  The gyros was very good along with the pitas they were served on. They were perfectly steamed and held the sandwich well even with the refreshing tzatziki sauce.  It was hit or miss but it's very new so I would try it again in a few weeks.
